column3: Test question
A - is there a significant difference in the mean average age between the two groups
B - is there a significant difference in the two genders between the two groups
C - is there a significant difference in patients having surgery for reason 1,2,3,4 or 5 between the two groups (ie 5 different statistical tests)
E - is there a significant difference in side of surgery, 1,2 or 3, between the two groups
F- is there a significant difference in ipsilateral degree of stenosis in the artery, 1,2,3,4,5, between the two groups
G - is there a significant difference in contralateral degree of stenosis in the artery, 0,1,2,3,4,5,6 between the two groups
H - is there a significant difference in previous ipsilateral surgery (Y/N) between the two groups
I - is there a significant difference in previous contralateral surgery (Y/N) between the two groups
J - is there a significant difference in each of the comorbidities (1-9) between the two patient groups
K - is there a significant difference in smoking status (1,2,3) between the two patient groups
L - is there a significant difference in the mean average creatinine between the two patient groups
M - is there a significant difference in the mean average ASA score between the two patient groups
N- is there a significant difference in AF (Y/N) between the two patient groups
O- Two patient groups
P- is there a significant difference in medications (1-9) between the two patient groups
Q - is there a significant difference in perioperative medications (1-3) between the two groups
R - is there a significant difference in perioperative thrombolysis (Y/N) between the two groups
S - is there a significant difference in mean average frailty score between the two groups
T - is there a significant difference in mean average time from symptoms to surgery between the two groups?
U - is there a significant difference in the anesthetic used (1-12) between the two groups?
V- is there a significant difference in the type of procedure (1-5) performed between the two groups?
W - is there a significant difference in the use of intraoperative shunt (Y/N) between the two groups
X - is there a significant difference in the post operative destination (1-4) between the two groups
Y - is there a significant difference in the mean average post operative stay in critical care between the two groups?
Z - is there a significant difference in return to theatre post operatively (Y/N) between the two groups?
AA- is there a significant difference in return to critical care post discharge (Y/N) between the two groups?
AB- is there a significant difference in the post operative complications (1-17) between the two groups?
AC - is there a significant difference in the type of post operative stroke (1/2) between the two groups?
AD - is there a significant difference in post operative nerve injury (Y/N) between the two groups?
AE - is there a significant difference in patient discharged alive or dead (1/2) between the two groups?
AF - is there a significant difference in the mean average length of stay between the two groups?
AG - is there a significant difference in 30 day readmission after discharge (Y/N) between the two groups?
AH - is there a significant difference in 30 day post discharge stroke (Y/N) between the two groups
AI - is there a significant difference in 30 day post op death (Y/N) between the two groups?
AJ - is there a significant difference in the mean average days to discharge?
